%md
# Overview
For this exercise we will work with the [Crimes in Chicago](https://www.kaggle.com/currie32/crimes-in-chicago) data set published on the Kaggle web site.

msg.data:
Overview

For this exercise we will work with the Crimes in Chicago data set published on the Kaggle web site.

paragraphs.text:
%md
# Installing kaggle-cli
The Kaggle web site requires authentication in order to download data the client must first obtain a token and then use the token to download the data set.  

1. Install the [kaggle-api](https://github.com/floydwch/kaggle-cli) on the Zeppelin server host and created a file containing the credentials in the zeppelin home directory. 
> ssh to zeppelin host
> sudo yum install libxml2-devel
> sudo yum install libxslt-devel
> sudo pip install kaggle-cli

msg.data:
Installing kaggle-cli

The Kaggle web site requires authentication in order to download data the client must first obtain a token and then use the token to download the data set.

  1. Install the kaggle-api on the Zeppelin server host and created a file containing the credentials in the zeppelin home directory.

    ssh to zeppelin host
    sudo yum install libxml2-devel
    sudo yum install libxslt-devel
    sudo pip install kaggle-cli

paragraphs.text:
%md
# Download and Store the Kaggle Chicago Crimes Data Set

msg.data: Download and Store the Kaggle Chicago Crimes Data Set

paragraphs.text:
%sh
echo "check for the kaggle credentials.  If this paragraph returns an authorization error, log in as zeppelin and check the contents of the file.  Should contain two lines.  First list is user name and second line is password."
ls -l ~/kagglecred

tmp_dir=$(mktemp -d -t zeppelinXXXXX)
crime_dir=$tmp_dir/data/crime
mkdir -p $crime_dir
cd $crime_dir

echo downloading data set from kaggle to $crime_dir
while read user; do
    read pw;
    kg dataset  -u $user  -p  $pw -d crimes-in-chicago -o currie32;
done < ~/kagglecred

echo "list downloaded files"
pwd
ls -lh

echo "files are actually zip files, change to zip extension"
for f in *.csv; do
   mv $f $f.zip
done


echo "moving to s3"
aws s3api create-bucket --bucket carolyndubywestodsc2017 --acl public-read
aws s3 sync $tmp_dir s3://carolyndubywestodsc2017

echo "deleting the temp directory"
cd ~
rm -rf $tmp_dir
